=head1 DESCRIPTION

Specifies minimal information for the solution offered to solve the
customer's business problem.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Arn => Str

The SolutionBase structure provides essential information about a
solution.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Catalog => Str

Specifies the catalog in which the solution is hosted, either C<AWS> or
C<Sandbox>. This helps partners differentiate between live solutions
and those in testing environments.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Category => Str

Specifies the solution category, which helps to categorize and organize
the solutions partners offer. Valid values: C<Software Product> |
C<Consulting Service> | C<Hardware Product> | C<Communications Product>
| C<Professional Service> | C<Managed Service> | C<Value-Added Resale
Amazon Web Services Service> | C<Distribution Service> | C<Training
Service> | C<Merger and Acquisition Advising Service>.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> CreatedDate => Str

Indicates the solution creation date. This is useful to track and
audit.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Id => Str

Enables the association of solutions (offerings) to opportunities.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Name => Str

Specifies the solution name.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Status => Str

Specifies the solution's current status, which indicates its state in
the system. Valid values: C<Active> | C<Inactive> | C<Draft>. The
status helps partners and Amazon Web Services track the solution's
lifecycle and availability. Filter for C<Active> solutions for
association to an opportunity.



